com.dukascopy.api.feed

Interface IFeedDescriptor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasePeriodFeedDescriptor, FeedDescriptor, PointAndFigureFeedDescriptor, RangeBarFeedDescriptor, RenkoFeedDescriptor, TickBarFeedDescriptor, TicksFeedDescriptor, TimePeriodAggregationFeedDescriptor

    public interface IFeedDescriptor
    Interface, which describes feed data.

    There might be several data types supported by JForex, see DataType

    Ticks are defined by
    DataType.TICKS (setter - setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument))

    Candles/Bars are defined by
    DataType.TIME_PERIOD_AGGREGATION setter - (setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument)),
    OfferSide (setter - setOfferSide(OfferSide)),
    Filter (setter - setFilter(Filter)),
    Period (setter - setPeriod(Period))

    RangeBars are defined by
    DataType.PRICE_RANGE_AGGREGATION (setter - setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument)),
    PriceRange (setter - setPriceRange(PriceRange)),
    OfferSide (setter - setOfferSide(OfferSide))

    Point and Figures are defined by
    DataType.POINT_AND_FIGURE (setter - setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument)),
    PriceRange called box size (setter - setPriceRange(PriceRange)),
    ReversalAmount (setter - setReversalAmount(ReversalAmount)),
    OfferSide (setter - setOfferSide(OfferSide))

    Tick Bars are defined by
    DataType.TICK_BAR (setter - setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument)),
    TickBarSize (setter - setTickBarSize(TickBarSize)),
    OfferSide (setter - setOfferSide(OfferSide))

    Renkos are defined by
    DataType.RENKO (setter - setDataType(DataType)),
    Instrument (setter - setInstrument(Instrument)),
    PriceRange called brick size (setter - setPriceRange(PriceRange)),
    OfferSide (setter - setOfferSide(OfferSide))

      • setDataType

        void setDataType(DataType dataType)
        Setter for data type. For price aggregation data types and tick bars (DataType.TICK_BAR, DataType.PRICE_RANGE_AGGREGATION, DataType.POINT_AND_FIGURE, DataType.RENKO) the given DataType is verified according to FeedDescriptor's period at data loading time, so if the dataType is not valid, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown at the data loading time.

        For previously mentioned data types period must be with the Unit.Day and the number of units must be 1 <= numOfUnits <= 7. Period shift must be in full hours and must be in range of [TimeUnit.HOURS.toMillis(-12),TimeUnit.HOURS.toMillis(12)].

        For DataType.TIME_PERIOD_AGGREGATION periods shift can be used for Period.DAILY or larger periods. If period shift is set for time period aggregation candles, then these candles do not start at 00:00 GMT, but according to the shift. E.g. if desired period is Period.DAILY and shift is TimeUnit.HOURS.toMillis(-3), then all candles will start at 21:00 GMT. Thus one can shift times for daily or larger candles according to his local time.

        Parameters:
        dataType -
